    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive profile, anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play, benefiting from a highly favorable park factor (+14%) against Ryan Feltner, whose projected xERA of 4.63 offers a prime opportunity for power production. Similarly, **Gunnar Henderson** occupies the lead-off spot with a significant surge in expected performance; while he faces a slight penalty for the opponent\u2019s elite control in the run game, his current trajectory and batting order placement make him indispensable despite a 31% rain risk at the stadium. **Andy Pages** also earns a high-confidence start (73.82) due to his own matchup with Feltner, with his scoring bolstered by the park environment and a favorable green light to steal against a pitcher with a slow delivery.\n\nStrategic benching remains critical in maintaining our category efficiency, and the most difficult decision involved **Brady House** (63.81). He was our top-scoring reserve, nearly displacing **Miguel Vargas** (64.21) or **Jackson Merrill** (55.56) in the starting nine. Ultimately, **Brady House** fell just short because the optimizer preferred the superior projected run-creation context surrounding **Miguel Vargas** in his specific lineup slot. We are also closely monitoring **Luis Robert Jr.** (59.35), whose score is suppressed by a difficult platoon split against Jameson Taillon; he stays in the lineup only because his speed-threat profile against a slow-working pitcher provides unique value in our 5x5 format. We continue to hold high-upside assets like **Jordan Westburg**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Liam Hicks** on the bench, waiting for optimal platoon alignment to deploy them in our bid to climb the standings.",
